      "span_text": "The first successful gene-based treatment of BardetBiedl syndrome-associated retinal degeneration was demonstrated in a Bbs4-null mouse model, where an AAV-based vector expressing BBS4 prevented photoreceptor death, improved retinal function, and visually evoked behavior responses, providing hope for a promising future therapy in humans"
